{"parse":{"title":"The Hand of the Violinist","pageid":51772350,"revid":800849404,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vevent\" style=\"width:22em;width: 22em; line-height: 1.4em; text-align: left; float:right;\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"summary\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; font-style: italic\">The Hand of the Violinist (The Rhythms of the Bow)</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:The_Hand_of_the_Violinist_(Balla_1912).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Hand of the Violinist (Balla 1912).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f6/The_Hand_of_the_Violinist_%28Balla_1912%29.jpg/300px-The_Hand_of_the_Violinist_%28Balla_1912%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"215\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f6/The_Hand_of_the_Violinist_%28Balla_1912%29.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"373\" data-file-height=\"267\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Artist</th><td class=\"attendee\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Giacomo_Balla\" title=\"Giacomo Balla\">Giacomo Balla</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Year</th><td>\n1912<span style=\"display:none\">&#160;(<span class=\"bday dtstart published updated\">1912</span>)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Medium</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Oil_paint\" title=\"Oil paint\">oil</a> on canvas</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Subject</th><td>\nThe hand of a <a href=\"/wiki/Violinist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Violinist\">violinist</a> in play</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Dimensions</th><td>\n56&#160;cm&#32;\u00d7&#160;78.3&#160;cm&#32;(22&#160;in&#32;\u00d7&#160;30.8&#160;in)<sup id=\"cite_ref-wikiart_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-wikiart-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.65em;\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Estorick_Collection_of_Modern_Italian_Art\" title=\"Estorick Collection of Modern Italian Art\">Estorick Collection of Modern Italian Art</a>, London</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Hand of the Violinist (The Rhythms of the Bow)</b></i> is a 1912 painting by Italian <a href=\"/wiki/Futurism\" title=\"Futurism\">Futurist</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Giacomo_Balla\" title=\"Giacomo Balla\">Giacomo Balla</a>, depicting a musician's hand and the neck of a <a href=\"/wiki/Violin\" title=\"Violin\">violin</a> \"made to look like it's vibrating through space\"\u2014blurred and duplicated to suggest the motion of frenetic playing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Independent_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Independent-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Opam_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Opam-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The painting, representative of Futurism's first wave, exhibits techniques of <a href=\"/wiki/Divisionism\" title=\"Divisionism\">Divisionism</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Greenwald_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Greenwald-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Balla was inspired to use multiplication to imply motion by the photographic experiments of <a href=\"/wiki/Eadweard_Muybridge\" title=\"Eadweard Muybridge\">Eadweard Muybridge</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/%C3%89tienne-Jules_Marey\" title=\"\u00c9tienne-Jules Marey\">\u00c9tienne-Jules Marey</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Greenwald_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Greenwald-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> As with other Futurists, he was also inspired by <a href=\"/wiki/Cubism\" title=\"Cubism\">Cubism</a>'s methods of capturing multiple perspectives; <i>The Hand of the Violinist</i> has been said to bring the viewer \"inside the reverberations of the instrument itself\", and has earned comparison with <a href=\"/wiki/Marcel_Duchamp\" title=\"Marcel Duchamp\">Marcel Duchamp</a>'s <i><a href=\"/wiki/Nude_Descending_A_Staircase\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nude Descending A Staircase\">Nude Descending A Staircase</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Bertrand_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Bertrand-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>From February to August 2014, the painting was part of the exhibit <i>Italian Futurism, 1909\u20131944: Reconstructing the Universe</i>, at the <a href=\"/wiki/Solomon_R._Guggenheim_Museum\" title=\"Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum\">Guggenheim</a> in New York.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Greenwald_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Greenwald-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Guggenheim_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Guggenheim-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Hand_of_the_Violinist&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-wikiart-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-wikiart_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.wikiart.org/en/giacomo-balla/the-hand-of-the-violinist-1912\">\"The Hand of the Violinist\"</a>. <i>WikiArt</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 September</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=WikiArt&amp;rft.atitle=The+Hand+of+the+Violinist&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wikiart.org%2Fen%2Fgiacomo-balla%2Fthe-hand-of-the-violinist-1912&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Hand+of+the+Violinist\" clas